# (Fedora) Stop the Kernel from updating


sudo nano /etc/dnf/dnf.conf

add the line

exclude=kernel-core,kernel,kernel-modules,kernel-modules-extra

then save the file


# BONUS
# Here is how to Remove kernels of version 6.0, for troubleshooting- in case you need that:
